{"status":"OK","result":{"originalLocale":"en","allowViewHistory":false,"creationTimeSeconds":1477238274,"rating":27,"authorHandle":"hellman_","modificationTimeSeconds":1477398226,"id":47948,"title":"\u003cp\u003eExpected size of a set consisting of pairwise AND from two random sets\u003c/p\u003e","locale":"en","content":"\u003cdiv class\u003d\"ttypography\"\u003e\u003cp\u003eHello everyone!\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eHere\u0027s an interesting problem. Sounds easy at first but I could not find a solution that matches experimental results. Maybe I am missing some simple observation.\u003c/p\u003e \u003chr /\u003e\u003cp\u003eYou are given two integers \u003cspan class\u003d\"tex-span\"\u003e1 ≤ \u003ci\u003el\u003c/i\u003e\u003csub class\u003d\"lower-index\"\u003e1\u003c/sub\u003e, \u003ci\u003el\u003c/i\u003e\u003csub class\u003d\"lower-index\"\u003e2\u003c/sub\u003e ≤ 2\u003csup class\u003d\"upper-index\"\u003e\u003ci\u003en\u003c/i\u003e\u003c/sup\u003e\u003c/span\u003e. Consider two random subsets of \u003cspan class\u003d\"tex-span\"\u003e\u003ci\u003en\u003c/i\u003e\u003c/span\u003e-bit vectors \u003cimg align\u003d\"middle\" class\u003d\"tex-formula\" src\u003d\"/predownloaded/75/92/759251f7defc6e524f110b51a56e30109b391b9a.png\" style\u003d\"max-width: 100.0%;max-height: 100.0%;\" /\u003e of sizes \u003cspan class\u003d\"tex-span\"\u003e\u003ci\u003el\u003c/i\u003e\u003csub class\u003d\"lower-index\"\u003e1\u003c/sub\u003e, \u003ci\u003el\u003c/i\u003e\u003csub class\u003d\"lower-index\"\u003e2\u003c/sub\u003e\u003c/span\u003e respectively. Let\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg align\u003d\"middle\" class\u003d\"tex-formula\" src\u003d\"/predownloaded/9e/19/9e19dc1da451c6eae2407826568e4fdade252036.png\" style\u003d\"max-width: 100.0%;max-height: 100.0%;\" /\u003e, where \u003cspan class\u003d\"tex-span\"\u003e\u0026amp;\u003c/span\u003e is a bitwise AND.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eCompute the expected size of \u003cspan class\u003d\"tex-span\"\u003e\u003ci\u003eR\u003c/i\u003e\u003c/span\u003e (in polynomial in \u003cspan class\u003d\"tex-span\"\u003e\u003ci\u003en\u003c/i\u003e\u003c/span\u003e time). Computing maximum possible size of \u003cspan class\u003d\"tex-span\"\u003e\u003ci\u003eR\u003c/i\u003e\u003c/span\u003e is interesting too.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eAn easier version is when bitwise AND is replaced by bitwise XOR, it is also interesting.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eNOTE:\u003c/strong\u003e I am not sure that this problem has a solution.\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e","tags":["bit manipulation","and","xor","probability","expectation"]}}